description: Triggered when an order is fulfilled.

docs.summary:
Triggered on successful creation of a new order. This means
the order has been validated and the payment has cleared,
and now the site owner can accept or cancel the order.

members.name: _id
members.doc: ID of the order to mark as `ACCEPTED`.

members.name: message
members.doc: Optional message added during order activity.

members.name: entityId
members.doc: ID of the entity associated with the event.

members.name: triggeredByAnonymizeRequest
members.doc: Whether the event was triggered as a result of a privacy regulation application (for example, [GDPR](https://support.wix.com/en/article/gdpr-frequently-asked-questions)). For advanced users.

members.name: _id
members.doc: ID of the order to mark as `CANCELED`.

members.name: catalogItemDescription
members.doc: Item description as defined in the catalog.

members.name: catalogItemId
members.doc: Line item ID as defined in the catalog.

members.name: catalogItemMedia
members.doc: Item media url as defined in the catalog.

members.name: catalogItemName
members.doc: Line item name as defined in the catalog.

members.name: promisedTime
members.doc:
Required - filter orders count by fulfillment promised time. (Latest delivery time promised by the restaurant)
Maximum supported range is up to 30 days.
NOTE: Count is a slow operation, for better performance request smaller time ranges.

members.name: status
members.doc: Required - filter orders count by status. Supported values: NEW, ACCEPTED

members.name: locationId
members.doc: Count orders only for a specific OS location ID

members.name: query
members.doc: Limit the count only for orders that match the query

members.name: restaurantLocationId
members.doc: Count orders only for a specific restaurant location

members.name: count
members.doc: Number of orders count that match the query

members.name: cursor
members.doc:
Pointer to the next or previous page in the list of results.

You can get the relevant cursor token
from the `pagingMetadata` object in the previous call's response.
Not relevant for the first request.

members.name: next
members.doc: Cursor pointing to next page in the list of results.

members.name: prev
members.doc: Cursor pointing to previous page in the list of results.

members.name: contactId
members.doc:
Customer's contact ID.
See [Contacts API](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/contacts/contacts/contacts-v4) for more details.

members.name: endTime
members.doc: Filter by date range, ending by a given timestamp

members.name: startTime
members.doc: Filter by date range, starting from given timestamp

members.name: approximate
members.doc: Whether an approximate address is used. Defaults to `false`. In case of `false` a house number is required.

members.name: comment
members.doc: Delivery Instructions added by the customer.

members.name: onArrival
members.doc: Special delivery instructions upon arrival to the address.

members.name: subdivision
members.doc: Subdivision. Usually a state, region, prefecture, or province code, according to [ISO 3166-2](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-2).

members.name: label
members.doc: Label of dine-in information added by the restaurant, e.g. `table` or `booth`.

members.name: value
members.doc: Value of dine-in information added by the restaurant, e.g. `#6`.

members.name: catalogDiscountDescription
members.doc:
Discount description as defined in the catalog.

Max: 1,000 characters

members.name: catalogDiscountId
members.doc: Discount ID as defined in the catalog.

members.name: catalogDiscountName
members.doc: Discount name as defined in the catalog.

members.name: contactless
members.doc: Whether the order is delivered contactless.

members.name: _id
members.doc: ID of the external delivery provider.

members.name: commission
members.doc: Fee paid by the restaurant to the external delivery provider.

members.name: customerFee
members.doc: Delivery fee charged to the customer.

members.name: name
members.doc: Name of the external delivery provider.

members.name: _id
members.doc: ID of the order to mark as `FULFILLED`.

members.name: asap
members.doc: Whether the order should be fulfilled as soon as possible. Defaults to `true`.

members.name: promisedTime
members.doc: Latest delivery time promised by the restaurant.

members.name: fieldMask
members.doc: Controls what data is returned in the response

members.name: _id
members.doc: ID of the order to retrieve.

members.name: fieldMask
members.doc:
Set of fields to retrieve.
Fields that aren't included in `fieldmaks.paths` are ignored.
See [the article about field masks](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/restaurants/orders/supported-field-masks)
for more details.

description: TEST This is the order response - where does this description appear...

members.name: locationId
members.doc: filter response to a specific location, otherwise return totals for all locations.

members.name: promisedTimeInProgress
members.doc: Order delivery date and time for filtering new orders count, Must include a `gte:` or `lte:` prefix, for example: `gte:2021-10-26T12:48:15Z`.

members.name: promisedTimeNew
members.doc: Order delivery date and time for filtering new orders count, Must include a `gte:` or `lte:` prefix, for example: `gte:2021-10-26T12:48:15Z`.

members.name: totals
members.doc: list of locationId's mapped to the total number of orders.

members.name: catalogReference
members.doc: References to the line item’s origin catalog.

members.name: comment
members.doc: Comment about the line item added by the customer.

members.name: dishOptions
members.doc: List of all dish options available for the line item.

members.name: availableChoices
members.doc: List of all available choices for the dish option.

members.name: defaultChoices
members.doc: List of dish option IDs selected by default.

members.name: maxChoices
members.doc: Maximum number of dish options the customer is allowed to choose.

members.name: minChoices
members.doc: Minimum number of dish options the customer is required to choose.

members.name: selectedChoices
members.doc: List of all dish options selected by the customer.

members.name: itemId
members.doc: Line item ID as defined in the catalog.

members.name: _createdDate
members.doc: Created date of the order epoch time.

members.name: fieldMask
members.doc: Controls what data is returned in the response.

members.name: sort
members.doc: Sorting of Orders in response. Default "CREATED_DATE:ASC"

members.name: status
members.doc: Order status to filter by. Currently Status Fulfilled is not supported

members.name: _createdDate
members.doc: Order creation date and time. Must include a `gte:` or `lte:` prefix, for example: `gte:2021-10-26T12:48:15Z`.

members.name: delivered
members.doc: Whether the order has been delivered.

members.name: fieldMask
members.doc:
Set of fields to retrieve.
Fields that aren't included in `fieldmaks.paths` are ignored.
See [the article about field masks](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/restaurants/orders/supported-field-masks)
for more details.

members.name: limit
members.doc: Number of orders to return. The minimum limit is 1, the maximum 1000.

members.name: locationIds
members.doc: Location filter. Pass an array of location IDs to return orders with any of the provided locations.

members.name: status
members.doc: Order status. Currently, it is not possible to filter by status `FULFILLED`.

members.name: appliedAmount
members.doc: Amount saved redeeming Wix Loyalty reward.

members.name: estimatedAccountBalance
members.doc:
Wix Loyalty estimated account point balance.
Equal to the sum of earned and adjusted points minus redeemed points.
The estimated point balance is the value before the order is completed. Following the purchase, the point balance is updated.

members.name: estimatedPointsEarned
members.doc:
Wix Loyalty estimated total earned points.
The estimated total earned points is the value before the order is completed. Following the purchase, the total is updated.

members.name: rewardRevision
members.doc:
Associated Wix Loyalty reward revision number, which increments by 1 each time the loyalty account is updated.

To prevent conflicting changes, the current revision must be passed when updating the loyalty account.
Ignored when creating an account.

members.name: currency
members.doc: Currency code. Must be valid ISO 4217 currency code (e.g., USD).

members.name: formattedValue
members.doc: Monetary amount. Decimal string in local format (e.g., 1 000,30). Optionally, a single (-), to indicate that the amount is negative.

members.name: value
members.doc: Monetary amount. Decimal string with a period as a decimal separator (e.g., 3.99). Optionally, a single (-), to indicate that the amount is negative.

description:
Money.
Default format to use. Sufficiently compliant with majority of standards: w3c, ISO 4217, ISO 20022, ISO 8583:2003.

members.name: _createdDate
members.doc: Order creation date and time in `yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:sssZ` format.

members.name: _updatedDate
members.doc: Date and time of order's latest update in `yyyy-mm-ddThh:mm:sssZ` format.

members.name: channelInfo
members.doc: Information about the sales channel that submitted the order.

members.name: comment
members.doc: Additional note to the order added by the customer.

members.name: lineItems
members.doc: Dishes and options included in the order.

members.name: loyaltyInfo
members.doc:
Information about the order’s loyalty points.
Learn more about the [Wix Loyalty Program](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/wix-loyalty-program/introduction).

members.name: count
members.doc: Number of items returned in the response.

members.name: cursors
members.doc: Cursors to navigate through the result pages using `next` and `prev`. Returned if cursor paging is used.

members.name: tooManyToCount
members.doc: Flag that indicates the server failed to calculate the `total` field.

members.name: total
members.doc: Total number of items that match the query. Returned if offset paging is used and the `tooManyToCount` flag is not set.

members.name: amount
members.doc: Amount paid using this payment type. Only differs from total amount paid in case of split payments.

members.name: providerTransactionId
members.doc:
Transaction ID.
See [Cashier API](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/wix-cashier/payments/transaction) for more details.

members.name: fee
members.doc: Pickup fee charged to the customer.

members.name: windowEndTime
members.doc: When a delivery must be picked up by. This is the end time of the pickup window.

members.name: windowStartTime
members.doc: When a delivery is ready to be picked up. This is the start time of the pickup window.

members.name: orderId
members.doc: ID of the order in the external provider.

members.name: fee
members.doc: The service fee's fee as Money.

members.name: tax
members.doc: The service fee's tax as Money.

members.name: delivery
members.doc: Total delivery fees charged to the customer.

members.name: loyaltySavings
members.doc: Total amount saved through the Wix Loyalty program.

members.name: subtotal
members.doc: Order subtotal. Calculated by substracting delivery fee, tax and discount from order total.
